<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_67a3ded9-06b2-41bb-8087-c57c7e40c094" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="SA"><sptc>B5D3</sptc><title id="_8cc0572c-86af-400d-a1bb-3ce7ec248850">Non-drinking water service</title><subclause id="_dcb2b816-00e9-4970-93fb-06221d1c3327" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_9be09403-19e6-492e-8741-9bcf22e7056b">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A hazard exists wherever it is possible for water or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1228_0.6.0.xml#_a7483c3c-cd8a-4c37-8f2b-8e4fba0e0989" id="_1f1651ec-c7df-436a-8640-16dc0a54646d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">contaminants</xref> to enter a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_6b4dc9ee-60f2-4901-85e3-c552c299ff01" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service or supply via any potential or actual <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1233_1.0.0.xml#_b3f409ec-8f72-48d9-8a64-0dc9d5fb5d67" id="_5921d9ac-e548-4b3a-a8d9-74c9fe7826e8" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">cross-connection</xref> between itself and another separate <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_0605a7b4-9eb3-480e-8cc6-d2314bbe61cc" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service on the same <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1463_0.4.0.xml#_fb3536f6-7ee5-4a29-a4da-402a8e1168dc" id="_e0cfedce-76d5-42c5-8862-a160c810d5a9" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">site</xref>.</p></subclause><subclause id="_e827915f-bd22-47cc-ae21-f6b1e82a1fb3" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_07efdbe2-2183-4763-9020-30faf8d16953">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>Each hazard must—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_7f803046-0f3b-466e-a0a2-1762b7c7eaa3">be assigned a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1332_3.6.0.xml#_e221b82c-bc4b-43d2-ab64-522dd5dd1885" id="_1c267b2d-b042-464f-8a4c-4df3c8872e8e" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">Hazard Rating</xref> in accordance with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_49ef982c-45dc-4a90-9596-f2b6fa0712a5" id="_00b1c4bf-ce4f-471a-ac97-754cbf2f6b94" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(10)</xref>, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_637c1753-6579-4f76-ab3e-826e43429458" id="_46833dae-d2a1-4807-beca-35ebfdbf8d04" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(11)</xref> or <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/9560_0.38.0.xml#_1c32bfcf-d609-42b0-981b-f4ea31656712" id="_025f752a-a7bf-4a68-94c3-0c35ba66d9b4" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="subclause">B5D7(12)</xref>; and</li><li id="_3297490e-9bf3-4924-8d38-bdec72acbe3c">be isolated from the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_909e8aea-3cf3-45d9-90d2-e77ad7ef704f" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service by appropriate protection which is selected and installed in accordance with AS/NZS 3500.1.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_4716747f-0d2e-4118-b42c-1f2d8b6a4f08" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_b841f9dd-ec9f-49b3-b2b8-6eb482f2d981">SubClause</title><num>3</num><p>If a drinking water service is interconnected with a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1378_4.3.0.xml#_cfc4fec0-3cb7-41d6-b176-4a92d4cdb221" id="_f7875690-72fc-4131-928c-07b0e2e03b3d" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">non-drinking water</xref> service for the purpose of emergency backup or to supplement, the <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_d5323c74-dfcf-40ef-8e00-5b21b99cc751" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> supply shall be fitted with a high hazard backflow prevention device at the point of interconnection as a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/8bd50c59-637c-4a79-8565-09cd674ed7ed/1527_28.0.0.xml#_fdc3535a-4b9d-49c2-add5-cb0a1b466b51" id="_be8213c7-cf1c-4dfa-82e9-4ba069f6869d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">zone protection</xref>.</p></subclause><callout id="_fcc368f8-cf03-47d2-adf6-56bd103beac3"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>The Office of the Technical Regulator has produced a document ‘Guidelines for Non-drinking water in South Australia’. The guidance document has been designed for the plumbing and water industries, water industry entities, and property owners with a non-drinking water supply.</p><p>The guidelines outline the requirements and responsibilities for installing, operating, and maintaining non-drinking water systems per the Water Industry Act 2012, Water Industry Regulations 2012, and appropriate technical standards.</p></callout></clause>